description: Measure voltages and inspect grounding at all biasing points and power supply connections in the ambient sensor module, including any decoupling capacitors, looking for abnormal voltages or unstable supply that might induce oscillation., outcome='The voltage measurements show expected high and low levels on the (+) and (−) labeled cables, with no sign of polarity inversion. However, the simulation did not converge and the circuit is reported as being in an unstable or oscillating state. This indicates abnormal circuit behavior was detected during measurement.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=105.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient sensor module (potentiometers and timing network),
description: Test the solder joints, continuity, and connection quality for the timing potentiometer and sensitivity potentiometer in the ambient sensor module, as well as any capacitors or timing network components. Oscillation may be caused by a floating or disconnected component in the timing or feedback path., outcome="The wiper terminals on both the Timing Potentiometer and Sensitivity Potentiometer are disconnected (floating). The other connections are: port 'p' to Control Input Cable (+), port 'n' to Control Input Cable (−) and Control Output Cable (−). No polarity inversion detected in these connections. The potentiometers do not have a defined resistance parameter.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=60.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
